label: A2B_mC12_12_2i_i-004
title: CaC$_{2}$-III Structure
comments:
This is a metastable room temperature structure. 
 The stable room temperature configuration has the \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B_tI6_139_e_a-001}{CaC$_{2}$-I ($C11_{a}$) structure}. 
 At low temperatures CaC$_{2}$ transforms into the \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B_mC12_15_f_e-001}{ThC$_{2}$ ($C_{g}$)} structure. 
 CaC$_{2}$-III shares the same AFLOW label, A2B\_mC12\_12\_2i\_i, with \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B_mC12_12_2i_i-006}{$\alpha$-Bi$_{2}$Pd} and \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B_mC12_12_2i_i-007}{OsGe$_{2}$} The structures are generated by the same symmetry operations with different sets of parameters ({\tt --params}) specified in their corresponding CIF files.
